# Routing

## URL map (v1)

| Path | Access | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| `/` | public | Home / landing |
| `/docs` | public | Documentation index (redirects to first category) |
| `/docs/category/[slug]` | public | Category section index listing child docs |
| `/docs/[slug]` | public | Single published doc |
| `/auth/login` | public | Session expired / sign-in via employee portal link |
| `/admin` | admin | Dashboard |
| `/admin/documents` | admin | Document list |
| `/admin/documents/new` | admin | Create document |
| `/admin/documents/[id]` | admin | CodeMirror editor |
| `/admin/categories` | admin | Category management |
| `/admin/settings` | admin | Site settings |
| `/api/auth/*` | public | Better Auth API + `POST /api/auth/logout` |
| `/api/document-media/[slug]` | public | Same-origin PDF proxy for in-page embeds |

## Groups

- **Public:** `/`, `/docs`, `/docs/*`, `/auth/login`
- **Protected:** `/admin`, `/admin/*` — `requireDocsAdmin()` in `admin/+layout.server.ts`
- **Unauthenticated admin:** redirect to employee portal login (`portalLoginUrl`)
- **Authenticated, no Docs access:** 403

## Conventions

- Use `resolve()` from `$app/paths` for internal links
- `/admin/**` uses `+layout.server.ts` for auth guard
- Unpublished docs return 404 for public; users with `canAccessDocsAdmin` can preview when signed in
